  "prompt": "What is potassium sorbate?",
  "response": "Potassium sorbate is a chemical compound that is widely used as a preservative in food and beverages to inhibit the growth of mold, yeast, and other microorganisms. Its chemical formula is C\u2086H\u2087KO\u2082. It is the potassium salt of sorbic acid and is effective in acidic environments, making it suitable for a variety of products including baked goods, dairy products, meats, and beverages.\n\nPotassium sorbate is known for its effectiveness, safety, and ease of use. It is generally recognized as safe (GRAS) by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) and is also approved for use in many other countries around the world.\n\nIn its pure form, potassium sorbate appears as a white crystalline powder. When used as a food additive, it helps extend the shelf life of products by keeping them free from spoilage caused by microorganisms.",
